DESCRIPTION
Execute gates during live runs (today capture-gate only records). A gate is attached to the guarded stage and has two seat kinds: CHECKS (deterministic runners; any failure = hard BLOCK, no threshold) and SEATS (model votes; weighted pass_threshold), each a runner invocation. Synthesize pass|rerun|escalated fail-closed (reuse etude-loop synthesis: any failed check blocks; <2 usable seats fails closed; errored seats skipped). rerun re-runs the guarded stage with feedback + bumps round (<stage>.r<round>); escalated climbs the tier. Auto-calls capture-gate. Reads gate config from the stage; seat/tier defs from the shared registry. Design: docs/plans/product/live-execution.md S2.

DESIGN
## Plan — etude-04i: Live gate execution

### Goal
Replace the no-op gate block in the live engine (engine.go:248-251, `gate %q deferred to etude-04i`) with real gate execution. After a guarded stage produces its output, fan that output across the gate's CHECKS (deterministic, hard veto) and SEATS (model votes, weighted threshold), synthesize a fail-closed verdict `pass | rerun | escalated` reusing the etude-loop / dogfood-runbook semantics, drive the loop (rerun re-runs the stage with feedback + bumps the round; escalated advances the registry tier ladder), and record each executed attempt as a `runmanifest.GateAttempt` appended to the run manifest via the SAME CAS manifest-write path the engine already uses for stages (manifest_version flips to 3 automatically on serialization, manifest.go:932-940).

